### Uninstallation

Just in case. There might be multiple ways to uninstall. These come to mind.

#### Windows

1. Find *Add or remove programs* by the start menu
1. Find NanoSupport and uninstall

#### Linux

Installation directory can be figured out by looking at file: `~/.local/share/applications/NanoSupport.desktop`

1. Remove installation directory
1. Remove `~/.local/share/applications/NanoSupport.desktop`

#### macOS

1. Simply move app bundle (and DMG?) to trash
